<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p>The approximate proportional change in 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i39">
   <mi>θ</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> from an epidemic is then
 <disp-formula id="uneq6">
  <math id="me8">
   <mo>−</mo>
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mfenced open="" close="|">
      <mrow>
       <mfrac>
        <mrow>
         <mi>d</mi>
         <mo>⁡</mo>
         <mi>log</mi>
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi>θ</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
           <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mi>d</mi>
         <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
        </mrow>
       </mfrac>
      </mrow>
     </mfenced>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mn>0</mn>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
   <mo>=</mo>
   <mfrac>
    <mrow>
     <mo>∫</mo>
     <mi>d</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>x</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mi>e</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>x</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mi>d</mi>
     <mi>x</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mo>∫</mo>
     <mi>ℓ</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>x</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mi>e</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>x</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mi>d</mi>
     <mi>x</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mfrac>
   <mo>=</mo>
   <mfrac>
    <mrow>
     <mi>H</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>A</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mfrac>
   <mo>.</mo>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>In this result, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i40">
   <mi>H</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is Keyfitz’s entropy, defined in ref. 
 <xref rid="r2" ref-type="bibr">2</xref>, and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i41">
   <mi>A</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the mean age of the stationary population
 <disp-formula id="uneq7">
  <math id="me9">
   <mi>A</mi>
   <mo>=</mo>
   <mfrac>
    <mrow>
     <mo>∫</mo>
     <mi>x</mi>
     <mi>ℓ</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>x</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mi>d</mi>
     <mi>x</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>e</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mn>0</mn>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mfrac>
   <mo>.</mo>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>In the United States, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i42">
   <mi>H</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is about 0.15 and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i43">
   <mi>A</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is about 40. If an epidemic produced an increase of 1/3 in mortality at all ages, (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i44">
   <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
   <mo>=</mo>
   <mn>1</mn>
   <mo>/</mo>
   <mn>3</mn>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>), this would cause a loss of life equal to 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i45">
   <mrow>
    <mo>(</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>/</mo>
     <mn>3</mn>
    </mrow>
    <mo>)</mo>
   </mrow>
   <mrow>
    <mo>(</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mn>0.15</mn>
    </mrow>
    <mo>)</mo>
   </mrow>
   <mo>/</mo>
   <mn>40</mn>
   <mo>=</mo>
   <mn>1</mn>
   <mo>/</mo>
   <mn>800</mn>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> of the remaining person years of life of the population.
</p>
